content.detailedDescription: In the night apears a biggest light in the sky, by the south.
content.summary: Big light with movement

content.detailedDescription: I was setting outside at the picnic table around 930 pm when i saw a bright light just appear like someone turned a light switch, it stayed stationary but changed shape and the light almost pulsate.I watched it for at least 5 minutes and then just like it appeared it was like someone flipped a light switch and it was gone.I went back out to the same area about 30 minutes later and about 10 minutes after i was out there i heard in the distance what sounded almost like a blow torch it was going across the field then i heard it turn and come right at me getting louder and louder, it was dark so i couldnt see and out of panic i ran inside and didnt go back out.
content.summary: Very bright light 4 times bigger and brighter than a star

content.detailedDescription: I was closing my bed room windows and getting ready to leave my house whaen i noticed a horizontal line of lights  (white) blinking sequentially. i watched for e few seconds and ran down stairs to get my brother in law, who was eating breakfast. we went out side and faced to the north and observed the line of lights moving away towards th north or northeast. there was no sound. the lights seemed to be at a high elevation as we observed a turbo prop aircraft (possible c2/e2) flying south and fly directly under these lights. we stood outside for several minutes and watched the lights fly away very slowly. at one time the lights flashed as if they were flashing around the perimeter of an abject, then they flashed from side to side.
content.summary: Series of flashing pulsating lights in a straight line moving to the northeast

content.detailedDescription: We were standing outside our home in los lunas, nm when we, my husband and i (he noticed it first) first observed this very bright light in the ne sky. when we first saw it it was above our tree line, but then dropped down and we were then looking at it through the trees. it was about 6am when we first noticed it. it was in the ne and looked to be over the sandia mountains in abq, nm. it was very bright and appeared to be round and defused along the outside rim of the circle. it didn't appear to have moved other then dropping down when we initially saw it. we called a friend who lives about a mile down the road and they were sitting outside watching it as well. we wrote it off as a weather balloon until we watched the news. we did try to photograph it with my phone but it didn't come out.
content.summary: When we first observed this bright light" it was, from our vantage point, just above our tree line then dropped down and it was seen through the trees. watched it for a while. called a friend who lives about a mile down the road and they were watching it.

content.detailedDescription: I stepped outside for a cigarette, upon doing so i had seen the said object crossing the sky towards norfolk i. a. i immediately ran inside and got my mother who also witnessed the object crossing the sky....I observed it in flight for nearly 10 mins. as it headed towards norfolk.... living in the area ive become very familiar with nearly all of the aircraft that frequent the skies, and i can confirm that this was no normal aircraft...It had no i.D blinking lights, the size dwarfed normal passenger planes( which i had witnessed prior to the sighting and frequently observe) it was completely silent!
content.summary: Giant object, appeared larger than conventional commercial airliners....

content.detailedDescription:
I'm just going to answer your questions in order...

1) i was outside on my porch trying to stay cool. (it's been kind of hot on the central coast today)

2)i looked up and saw some lights ...Weird because they were strange bright lights that i have never seen before and the craft made no noise..

3) a plane

4) it seemed to accelerate...But the thing that made me most take notice that it was joined by two other objects (very bright lights) that seemed to accompany this craft into space....

5) it was a very unsettling experience...Kind of wish i did not see it..

6) they just faded away...

hope this helps, i'm just really interested if anybody else seen this.

thanks,

john
content.summary: Lower flying v shaped object with very bright pulsing lights. followed up by two bright star light objects following it exactly into the sky.

content.detailedDescription: They are west of tucson.We have seen then regularly.The orbs start with one and split into 2-5 orbs.We looked at them through night vision and they appear to be black orbs.
content.summary: Orange orbs

content.detailedDescription: Standing in my backyard facing west in surprise az; i saw a craft that reflected orange as the sun was setting. at first sight it looked stationary, but then it moved slowly north. it then moved back to its original position south and hovered for another few minutes. it then repeated the process of moving north then south. it hovered for about 2 minutes when it just suddenly disappeared. i live near luke air force where there are military jets as well as commercial jets that fly over 24/7 and it was not any of them. in addition, it could not have been a helicopter as they do not disappear. definitely strange, last seen heading toward tonopah.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Craft relfecting orange seen hover then slowly move north then south then north then south and disappear

content.detailedDescription: I saw a v-shaped object, with no flashing lights just soft pink lights. it floated above me coming from the 5 north at very fast rate of speed. i saw  this object 5 times within 1 ur. and 15 minutes. the last time i saw this object i could see it had a body  that seemed blackbut shiney. one time it flew overhead with only .One light on, on it's left sideand several on the right. another time an orb or flash of light left the formation at high rate of speed. i have been a stargazer most of my life and i have never seen the skies so busy with unusual lights   over amarillo like the last month.These objects lasted only seconds visibilityas they moved quickly and suddenly vanish.
content.summary: Saw v-shape object, no flashing lights, pink lights, no less than 5 times directly overhead, amount of lights differ each time

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving home from parkersburg, wv on rt 7 north in ohio.  i happened to look up and to the left and noticed to lights space appros a thumbs width apart proceeding in a northeasterly direction at approx 55 mph.  initially i thought it could be lifeflight going to wetzel co. hospital, but it was moving too slow for lifeflight and from the wrong direction.  the lights proceeded ne along the ohio river, never changing direction but moving at a steady speed.  i thought if it were lifeflight it would begin descending once it got close to the hospital, but it didn't.  
the only feeling i have are just curiosity.  i know what it wasn't, but have no idea what it was/is.  eventually the object appeared to hover over the hills ne of town and i noticed that between the two bright lights on either side there were three lights of less intensity of brightness.  after watching for approx 5 minutes longer i came inside and at that time the lights were still stationary.  i checked again after doing some chores ( about 5 mn) and the lights were still there.
content.summary: I observed lights moving in ne direction an a relatively low x speed for approx 30 mn.  object eventually became stationary ne or new martinsville wv

content.detailedDescription: About 11pm looking at the night sky saw red and green blinking lights.  got my camera so i could enlarge. put on night mode (samsung galaxy 4).  once enlarged i could make out the shape and lights much clearer.  disc shape with top and bottom domes.  i also saw what looked like little stars or balls of light around it coming and going (almost reminded me of swarming mosquitoes), one turned a bright red for just a second.  kept moving in a line further away until i could not see anymore (took about an hour from when i first noticed it).  disappeared out of sight or went behind trees i could not tell which happened first.  lucky to see it by about 12:40 it became overcast in our area.
content.summary: Looking at stars noticed blinking got my samsung galaxy 4 to take pic and enlarge

content.detailedDescription: 3 f16s screaming to the west of my house were chasing after 5 flashing ufos  near the stephenville area. they appeared to play a cat and mouse game for a few minutes teasing each other and then headed off to the northeast i thought i had some video but it seems that it turned out to be shaky and non descript sorry i didnt get video, but my wife and i witnessed this event.
content.summary: 5 ufos chased by 3 f16s near the stevenville area

content.detailedDescription: On way to work driving 55mph, icy road conditions, very dark, no moon, no street lights. approaching a left hand curve on kenai spur hwy just before fire station #2. with my car about 1500 ft from hwy curve ahead i saw a large dull burnt orange colored object out my front windshield (driver side) stationary above a treeline on north side of hwy; a few houses are scattered below the treeline. i initially thought it was an old microwave tower with its drum shaped domes (3 side by side) illiminated from below by flood lights. i thought the dull orange color was odd, and the "3 drums" i assumed was the top of a microwave tower looked too tight together with the middle one being the largest. i would estimate what i saw to be about 80 ft across and about 40 feet high at center. the trees below it where not illuminated by the object, it had a clear edge to it with black sky beyond, it had 3 rectangular black marks on the right side and a black vertical line going from right to left down the center. as i entered the road curve and come to about 500 ft from the object i could see it was certainly not an old microwave tower with their classic fabric covered drums. i took my eyes off it to watch the road ahead when it was just above my rear view mirror on windshield, it was about twice the size of the rear view mirror from my position looking out at it. i have driven this hwy for many years and realised no tower is at this location. i could not stop quickly due to the icy road conditions, i had to continue on thru the curve until the road straightenned out. about a minute elapsed with the object behind me and out of my sight before i could stop, turn around and drive back to site by side of hwy. while turning around on hwy to go back i could not see anything in the area it had been down the road, just dark sky and a few dull porch lights on the scattering of houses below the treeline. it was gone, i had not seen it move away. later in the daylight i drove back and confirmed what i thought, that no tower of any kind is at the location in question; just a 100 ft wide treeline on north side of hwy with a few houses below and a small lake beyond this. i have not seen anything like this since, on my many drives to the kenai peninsula each year. i had a camera at the time on the car seat(iphone), but in the brief time i could have taken a shot i did not think "ufo" i really thought i was seeing a old microwave tower that was illuminated, very frustrating to have missed such an opportunity to say the least.
content.summary: Rounding curve on hwy, saw a burnt orange colored object over n tree line

content.detailedDescription: I just happened to be out in my backyard watering flowers when i looked up saw a light moving from south to north.  i didn't have any flashing lights like a plane or jet have and it did not make a sound when it went over.  i saw 4 of them monday night on 9-23.  one and then about half and hour later another moving from south to north.  then two more moving from north to south.  aren't jets suppose to have flashing lights on its underside and wingtips?  well, these didn't have any flashing lights or sound like most jets have when they fly over.  this happened between 9 and 10 at night.  i'm just trying to figure out what the objects where that i saw.  i don't think they were jets unless they where drones, but these where at a real high altitude.  i would say as high or higher than jets fly.  i had a pair of binoculars to try to zoom in on them but i couldn't get close enough to see what they were.  i need to get a high powered telescope or binoculars.  did i actually see a ufo or was it something else?  curiousity is killing me!
content.summary: Just a bright light moving from north to south.  no flashing light and no sound

content.detailedDescription: At aprox. 8:51 mdt observerved fireball south of wolf point , mt. came down bright then turned to green then looked liked it exploded way to the south of us  my brothetr called me 10 minutes later and said he was going to billings and was at circle , mt. circle is 55 miles south of wolf point - and he saw a bright fire ball right in front of them that turned green an exploded into about 15 pieces-freaked him out - but we are 50 miles north of where he was at and we saw this excactly how he describe it dont know if it was a ufo or meteorite    but please get back to me if it is something else or seen by someone else
content.summary: Dont know if  ufo but came down fireball then turn green and exploded

content.detailedDescription: Let dog out in backyard and noticed what appeared to be an elongated star. noticed one yesterday in western sky, however, did not really pay much attention to it. today however, i noted a similar sight in the ne sky over lake erie. looked to the w and noted same object as yesterday. paying attention to the ne object i began to notice movement with the directions constantly changing. i had a clear view between the branches of two tree, there is absolutely no question in regards to the movement or the various direction changes. during this time period i also noted an plane flying (well up in the sky) and was able to note the difference in the 2 movement patterns. what i saw was definitely not a plane or a star. i lost contact when i re-entered my house. i am 68 years old and look into the sky often, this is the first time i have seen something i cannot explain.
content.summary: Two objects, w and ne  sku, elonged starlike, noted movement varying speed/direction.

content.detailedDescription: At approx 8:15 pm on 9/23/13, we were headed south on joslyn road when my daughter noticed a bright light in the sky. we thought it may be a shooting star when we seen another plane oe helicopter with what looked like blinking red lights headed directly in the path of this object.  i jokingly said look there going to hit each other! it looked as if they collided and the glowing bright object began to fall.  it looked like it was falling in slow motion.  we watched it continue to fall until it was beyond the tree line..Needless to say the other 3 people in the car were beyond freaked out!!!!!
content.summary: Saw what we thought was a star burning out , then saw a helicopter hit it and watched it fall from sky

content.detailedDescription: Observed a slow pulsating blue light coming from the west in the southern sky.  proceeded to go east.  stopped for approximately 5 minutes.  then proceeded north. watched for approximately 25 minutes.
content.summary: Pulsating blue light

content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were sitting in our backyard when she asked what is that? i looked and saw four lights, two red on the inside two green on the outside all in a horizontal line.The object was motionless, just hovering. it quickly moved to the right,hesitated the moved back to the left. at this point it dropped suddenly the came back up there was no audible noise. it continued to make these types of movements and during this time kept moving away from us in a northern direction/ it did that until it was out of sight/we got in the car and drove about three miles and spotted an object we believed to be what we saw earlier we then went and talked to our local newspaper guy/ the object had moved west so it was now visable from our house/ the newspaper guy lives next to us and we pointed it out to him. he got his recorder and stayed on his porch while my wife and i drove west. at that point we observed the object for about five mjnutes. we went back to the neighbors house to see if he wanted to drive out with us and he declined. my wife and i went back at  that point we saw six similar light configurations all in different directions. compared to what we saw once we drove outside of town. the similarity was the red and green lights and the fact that they appeared to be motionless except for slight movement horizontally and vertically. in conversations with people today i was told of a woman who lives in goliad which is 30 minutes from here who was levitated by an unknown object and another who sees objects move across her pasture frequently
content.summary: Seemed close hovered changed direction horizontily and vertically went away  then up then down  then up and moved north

content.detailedDescription: We were driving along doansburg rd.In brewster,ny heading towards putnam lake(which is on the border of brewster and patterson) and i noticed a neon green acorn or sphere shaped object going over green chimneys farm/complex. it was very bright but not blinding. it did not leave a trail. i have never seen anything like that in my life and neither had my husband. i was startled and looked at my husband and said what the hell is that. he looked up and we were both stunned. it seemed to be traveling kind of fast and we watched as it descended towards the other side of the road until it was out of sight. we then pulled the car over and really didn't know what to make of it. i wrote on my facebook page and asked if anyone in that area had seen anything (highly populated area) and nobody else had seen it. after we went to the store we decided to head in the direction that we saw it heading. we saw nothing that indicated any landing or crash. it would be great to know if this was some type of ufo or some kind of meteor or shooting star. i have seen meteors and shooting stars and none have ever looked the way this looked. this thing spooked us quite a bit and we haven't stopped thinking about it. we actually called the police department to see if anyone else reported anything and they said no. hoping for some answers from you. thanks!
content.summary: We were driving and spotted a green acorn shaped object in the sky

content.detailedDescription: I was in my front yard and i was filming the in coming delta jet that was landing at atl airport.
content.summary: Ufo files through delta airlines airplane in the middle of the after noon

content.detailedDescription: I was at my friends house on his deck smoking cigars like we have been doing for many years. we always look up at the sky at planes, hot air balloons, flocks of birds, normal everyday stuff. then my friend noticed 2 objects in the sky coming from the north part of the sky moving south on a straight line. we have seen planes of all sizes, hot air balloons from the neighboring towns, and other aircraft. they all have a color even at a far distance. i said that they look weird, they were glowing orange and they were both moving together. we expected them to just continue moving south as they were but all of a sudden the both went straight up very quickly, descending to the left just as quick, and then moved around a little bit then they both went back on their original path. my friend ran and got his camera, he has a long distance lens on it and snapped a couple of really clear pics. the continued moving south and we lost them in the trees. we were so excited to witness this but to get some pics was the best part!
content.summary: Saw 2 glowing orange lights, went up, down, left, then west.

content.detailedDescription: It was the second night i noticed this star shape light ...That was larger than a star overlooking my neighborhood, above a hill. i could not see from street level, but shot many video's from 2nd floor window. it looked like many large ships and than smaller ones come across the screen. amazing. i included this short clip and have much more footage if your interested in looking into this further.
content.shape: Boomerang,   Cigar,   Cone,   Cylinder,   Disc,   Fireball,   Star-like,   Teardrop,   Triangle
content.summary: Reno nv 9/22/13 - many ships - amazing video

content.altitude: Treetop, 500 Feet or Less, Over 500 Feet (under cloudcover), Over 500 Feet (no cloudcover)
content.detailedDescription: I observed the craft while standing in my garage door entry-way at approximately 8pm. the ufo initially passed over my home in a westward (east to west) direction. i initially noticed the object as it was very bright white in color. it had no strobes like a helicopter or airplane. i had expected it to be a plane or helicopter at initial glance. i watched its flight path thinking it was just going to continue on as most usual aircraft do when passing but this craft stopped and stayed in one location and hovered for about 15-20 minutes and did not move from the location. i did not take my eyes off of it. i have personally observed helicopters hovering but usually they change location of hover and give a very distinctive rotor sound. this craft had no sound. i live in a heavily wooded area and i could see that its position did not change because i could gauge its location/movement against the trees/branches it was above. i estimated the craft to be less than 1000ft from the ground. the object was diamond in shape, white top and bottom with the center pulsating and omitting a bright bluish white light. the weather was rainy with light cloud cover. i could initially see the object with no clouds surrounding it yet there was enough light to see some clouds pass in front of it on occasion. the object seemed to change shape from roundish fuzzy white exterior to a more distinct diamond shape. i had gone to retrieve my cell phone and binoculars to see it or photograph it. i could not get a clear enough photo with my cell phone due to the darkness and limited distance magnification. i was able to observe the craft through low magnification binoculars but could not make any further determination than seeing it with the naked eye. i do have 20/20 vision. i lost sight of the object after returning from inside my house after the initial 20 minutes of it being there.
content.summary: Ufo hovering 20 minutes

content.detailedDescription: Driving west after a very short, yet intense rain/thunder lightning storm. looked up in the southwestern sky just by habit & among the stars saw this amazing formation of orange lights. i thought they were a "city in the sky". they were brighter and bigger than the stars. i could not tell if they were moving. they were fairly close to eachother, resembling a sort of orion's belt type proximity to one another. right before i noticed them i was feeling extremely happy & grounded. as i was looking at them, this feeling of happiness started to very much increase in my body & also an apprehensive feeling arose inside of me. i wanted to see if other people were seeing them so i pulled in to a grocery store parking lot & as i was getting the attention of the first person i saw, the lights faded away. i've never seen anything like this before and it was an exciting yet eerie sight.
content.summary: Looked like a city in the sky. bright orange. specific formation. faded when i tried to show someone else.

content.detailedDescription: Observed enveloped by a cloud then vanish.
content.summary: Observed enveloped by a cloud then vanish.

i saw a star explode in second like a big explossion in a half of 1second too far with no sound

in a couple of milli second all came to normal and the star was disappear.

content.detailedDescription: I was heading to greene county at lexington rd at 6:20am as i was driving under a green light i caught 5 long light fly a straigt in the sky over my car and i could tell it had no noise and was not a plane or helicopter of any type! it was fast and caught my eye because i have never witnessed anything like this before! as it flew over me it eventually disappeared over the tree line! i was in awe that i just encounterd a ufo! it eas long rectangle lights in a straight path and was multi-collard ad it was huge something that low you should off heard a noise but nothing was heard! very weird to say the most!
content.summary: Driving down lexington rd and a row of long light flew straight ahead in a row

content.detailedDescription:
It was a pretty spring day like any other. my partner and i stepped out into the back yard 6pm-ish  to walk the dogs (to get the dogs out of the house while their kibble dinner is being made) like we regularly do every day. sooo... my partner and i are standing at the end of our dock (on cedar creek lake)  facing west when it came into our vision out of the south moving very slowly. at first we thought japanese balloon lantern, then it appeared to move north like 20-25 miles in a couple seconds and slowed again.  it was so amazing it was hard for me to tear myself away to get a camera. i still ran to get a camera. i ran back out side and it was still slowing moving (positioned north west from us), i start to fire up the camera and by the time the camera booted up it turned away from us and departed very quickly.  it was burnt orange with a orange "aura"  . as far as our feelings. i was amazed when i realized what it was seeing, then afterwords i had a range of emotions at the same time like a manopausal anxiety attack. (not from the ufo) more so my brain having to totally re-wire it's self to even process it and accept it.

my partner doesn't like to discuss it, but i think had similar emotions. he thinks a fleet of black suburbans filled with guys in white lab coats and butterfly nets is going to show up and pick us up.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Quite amazing!  a little frightening, made me change how i discern info on the subject!

content.detailedDescription: Large disc shaped spacecraft seen thru occasional breaks in cloud cover hovering over music hall in cincinnati, ohio on friday september 20, 2013 from 7pm until sunday september 22, 2013 at 7pm
content.summary: Disc shaped ufo seen hovering over music hall on friday september 20, 2013 from 7pm until sunday september 22, 2013 at 7pm
